details.Clock: Running memory at 2x clock to support more concurrent ports

Additional information.text: RAM usage is increased from 4 RAMs to 8 RAMs because the width of individual RAM blocks in true dual-port mode is limited to 20 bits.
Requested size 1024 bytes, implemented size 8192 bytes, stall-free, 4 reads and 3 writes.
For each replicate, 2 private copies were created to efficiently support multiple simultaneous workgroups. This resulted in no increase in actual block RAM usage.
For each bank, 4 replicates were created to efficiently support multiple accesses. To reduce this factor, reduce number of read and write accesses.
